
---Links---
* http://dev.mysql.com/doc/refman/5.0/en/mac-os-x-installation.html
* http://dev.mysql.com/doc/refman/5.0/en/unix-post-installation.html (for cleanup of data dir)
* http://dev.mysql.com/doc/refman/5.0/en/default-privileges.html (for setting passwords)

---Deployment---
(1) Current location
* the install in de/deploy is not used.
* install_dir: /usr/local/mysql
* auto-start variable: /etc/hostconfig   MYSQLCOM=-YES-
(2) Reinitialize if not able to start mysql (all DB will be deleted!) 
* startup errors
  Can't find file: './mysql/host.frm
* rm -rf install_dir/data
* sudo scripts/mysql_install_db --user=mysql
  Important to use mysql as a user so as to have correct permissions
* check passwords
  bin/mysql -u root
  SELECT User, Host, Password FROM mysql.user;
* set passwords
  bin/mysqladmin -u root password root
(3) Enabling PDO extension for PHP, Symfony
* https://discussions.apple.com/thread/1539743?start=0&tstart=0

---Usage---
(1) Startup
* if auto-start "YES", 
  "sudo /Library/StartupItems/MySQLCOM/MySQLCOM start"
* else 
  sudo su -
  cd install_dir
  ./bin/mysqld_safe --user=mysql &
(2) Commands
* bin/mysql -u root -p
  (do not enter password after -p, it will prompt for the password)
  password is "root"
* Use <database>;
* show tables;
* System database
  use mysql;
  select user, host from user;
(3) Strutsweb (In mysql prompt)
* create database strutsweb;
* use strutsweb;
* source <sql file>
